BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:VmcrWBzL0UVoR1hZ9TwGH
SUMMARY:Coworking Open House Week @ The Cloud Room
DTSTAMP:20260413T005336Z
DTSTART:20260413T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Curious about coworking and looking for the perfect spot to get
	 work done and reach your goals? Join us for a complimentary day during ou
	r upcoming Open House Week and experience what it’s like to be a part of o
	ur incredible community!\n\nWhat's Included:\n\nOne Free Trial Day: Pick a
	ny day during Open House Week to try out our coworking space\, free of cha
	rge! Arrive anytime 9am or later — whatever works best with your schedule.
	\n\nAccess to our beautiful workspace including quiet desk space with moni
	tors\, large lounge area\, phone booths\, bar\, and outdoor patio.\n\nComp
	limentary coffee\, tea\, snacks and kombucha.\n\nHigh-speed Wi-Fi\, printi
	ng\, and meeting rooms available for rent\n\nThe chance to meet like-minde
	d professionals and get a feel for the Cloud Room vibe.\n\nSpecial Offer:\
	n\nIf you love your free day with us and decide to become a member\, we’ll
	 waive your initiation fees when you sign up! How to Join:\n\nReserve your
	 free trial day by selecting one day of your choice on our Calendly \\(one
	 free trial day per person\\)\n\nShow up and enjoy your day at Cloud Room!
	 Be sure to check in with the staff at the front of the lounge so we can g
	ive you a quick tour of the space and get you set up with the wifi.\n\nSig
	n up for membership to take advantage of waived initiation fees.\n\nDon’t 
	miss this chance to test out our space\, meet amazing people\, and see if 
	Cloud Room is the perfect fit for your work needs!\n\nCurrent Promotions:\
	n\n⭐️ Sign up for a grounded membership and get your first month free \\+ 1
	0% off you first year of membership. 3 month commitment required.\n\n⭐️ Flo
	ating Membership Promo: Take 50% off your first full month of floating mem
	bership.\n\nSpaces are limited—RSVP today.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com
	/events/#/details/coworking-open-house-week-the-cloud-room/18423258/2026-0
	4-13T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/coworking-open-house-week
	-the-cloud-room/18423258/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:The Cloud Room\, 1424 11th Ave Suite 400\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ab7Mu-sF-9PmrZzpGSDel
SUMMARY:Spy Maters Camp II
DTSTAMP:20260413T005336Z
DTSTART:20260413T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:Calling all young secret agents! This time kids are welcome to 
	join action-packed Outdoor Spy Camp\, where kids will train to become top-
	notch spies through thrilling challenges\, daring missions\, and teamwork!
	 Obstacle Courses & Ninja Training – Agents-in-training will test their ag
	ility\, speed\, and stealth as they navigate exciting ninja courses\, craw
	l through the forest and learn to use nature objects to complete the chall
	enge. Scavenger Hunts & Riddle Solving – Spies must sharpen their detectiv
	e skills by decoding secret messages\, solving riddles\, and uncovering hi
	dden clues to complete their top-secret missions. Nerf Battles & Tactical 
	Challenges – Gear up for friendly Nerf wars\, where teamwork and strategy 
	are key to outsmarting the opposition. Agents will also practice their pre
	cision and accuracy with target practice and stealth maneuvers. Escape Roo
	m-Style Puzzles – Secret agents will work together to crack codes\, unlock
	 treasure chests\, and solve mind-bending puzzles before time runs out! Ou
	tdoor Adventure & Camouflage Training – Spies will blend into their surrou
	ndings\, practice silent movement\, and use nature to their advantage whil
	e completing their missions. This high-energy camp is perfect for kids who
	 love adventure\, problem-solving\, and action-packed fun in the great out
	doors! Are you ready to accept the mission? - follow the link to book a sp
	ot!\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/spy-maters-camp-ii/18
	306068/2026-04-13T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/spy-maters-camp-ii/183060
	68/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:Suncatcher Forest School\, 18701 se 60th st\, Issaquah\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:No3TPqbb2JPMMv_hsmEpj
SUMMARY:La Hora de Cuentos Familiares
DTSTAMP:20260413T005336Z
DTSTART:20260413T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, April 13\, 2026\, 10:30 - 11am\n\nDurante la hora de c
	uentos\, los niños de 0 a 5 años y sus familias pueden disfrutar de histor
	ias\, canciones y divertidas actividades de aprendizaje.\n\nEvento en espa
	ñol.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Área para niño
	s\n\nRegistration Required: No se requiere inscripción.\n\nDetailed Descri
	ption: El aprendizaje temprano es una excelente manera para que los niños 
	de 0 a 5 años y sus familias desarrollen habilidades de aprendizaje\, alfa
	betización y lenguaje\, así como una comunidad con otras familias.\, Leemo
	s cuentos\, cantamos canciones y tenemos actividades educativas atractivas
	 que ayudan a los niños y sus cuidadores a crecer juntos.\,\n\n-----------
	--------------------------------------------\, At storytime\, kids ages 0-
	5 and their families can enjoy stories\, songs\, and fun learning activiti
	es.\, Early Learning is a great way for kids ages 0-5 and their families t
	o develop learning\, literacy\, and language skills as well as community w
	ith other families.\, We read stories\, sing songs\, and have engaging\, e
	ducational activities that help kids and their caregivers grow together.\n
	\nEvent Logistics: Este evento se llevará a cabo en español.\, No se requi
	ere inscripción\, pero estos programas son muy populares y la capacidad de
	 la sala puede llenarse rápidamente.\, Las familias de todas las edades so
	n bienvenidas\, aunque este programa de aprendizaje temprano está diseñado
	 para niños de 0 a 5 años\, sus cuidadores y familias.\, Obtenga más infor
	mación sobre los programas\n\nAprendizaje temprano y la hora de cuentos .\
	,\n\n-------------------------------------------------------\, This event 
	will take place in Spanish.\, Registration is not required but these progr
	ams are very popular and the room capacity can fill up quickly.\, Families
	 of all ages are welcome\, though this early learning program is intended 
	for youth aged 0-5\, their caregivers and families.Find out more about\n\n
	Early Learning & Story Time\n\nprograms.\n\nContact Us: Si tiene alguna pr
	egunta sobre este evento\,\n\npregúntenos\n\no llame al 206-386-4636.\,\n\
	n-------------------------------------------------------\, If you have que
	stions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accomm
	odations: Podemos ofrecer acomodamiento para personas con discapacidades e
	n los eventos de la biblioteca. Póngase encontacto con\n\nLEAP\n\nal menos
	 siete días antes del evento para solicitar acomodamiento.\, Todos los pro
	gramas de la biblioteca son gratuitos y abiertos al público.\,\n\n--------
	-----------------------------------------------\, We can provide accommoda
	tions for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEA
	P\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.All Li
	brary programs are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcit
	y.com/events/#/details/la-hora-de-cuentos-familiares/18572477/2026-04-13T0
	0
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/la-hora-de-cuentos-famili
	ares/18572477/2026-04-13T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:M096XrBXYqyKLuNsTRloI
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260413T005336Z
DTSTART:20260413T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, April 13\, 2026\, 11am - 5pm\n\nTrained volunteers wil
	l be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nLo
	cation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 5 - Mixing Chamber
	 Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nD
	etailed Description: Drop-in tax help is offered on a first-come\, first-s
	erved basis.\, This service is free and available to individuals only.\, T
	he free service is not available for business tax returns.\, To receive ta
	x help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired Documents:\n\nPhoto 
	identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Identificati
	on Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\, Proof of inc
	ome\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Officia
	l documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \
	\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to prov
	ide information about health care coverage for each person on the return\,
	\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year's tax return\, if available\, Bank account a
	nd routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer
	 print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, Due to federal b
	udget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain tax forms
	 and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww
	.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms from Li
	brary computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nUnited W
	ay of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locations serv
	e anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\,000 fo
	r non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United Way at 
	206-461-3700.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nA
	sk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accom
	modations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontac
	tLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\,
	 All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-04-13T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-04-13T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
